1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,521
Previously on Doctor Who...

2
00:00:02,641 --> 00:00:04,081
C: Over the past week,
there's been a spate of attacks

3
00:00:04,201 --> 00:00:06,721
on intelligence officers
worldwide,

4
00:00:06,841 --> 00:00:08,121
of every nationality.

5
00:00:09,081 --> 00:00:11,841
We need your help...Doctor.

6
00:00:12,521 --> 00:00:14,081
SAY NAN: Die, die, die...

7
00:00:14,201 --> 00:00:17,201
(SCREAMING)

8
00:00:18,921 --> 00:00:21,321
YAZ: Daniel Barton.
Born in Bromsgrove,

9
00:00:21,441 --> 00:00:23,601
now lives just north
of San Francisco.

10
00:00:23,721 --> 00:00:25,241
- He's the founder of VOR.
- You can't entirely

11
00:00:25,361 --> 00:00:26,321
trust everyone.

12
00:00:26,441 --> 00:00:27,881
YAZ: Only 93% human.

13
00:00:28,001 --> 00:00:29,361
- What's the other 7%?
- We're going to need

14
00:00:29,481 --> 00:00:30,401
your best man on this.

15
00:00:30,521 --> 00:00:31,961
- What do you call him?
- 0.

16
00:00:32,081 --> 00:00:33,601
(WINDOW SHATTERS)

17
00:00:33,721 --> 00:00:34,721
O...

18
00:00:36,281 --> 00:00:36,841
(WINDOWS SHATTER)

19
00:00:36,961 --> 00:00:38,641
What have you brought here,
Doctor?

20
00:00:40,441 --> 00:00:41,881
Where are you from?

21
00:00:42,001 --> 00:00:43,441
CREATURE: Far beyond.

22
00:00:44,081 --> 00:00:44,921
(SCREAMS)

23
00:00:45,041 --> 00:00:46,801
Ryan?!

24
00:00:47,961 --> 00:00:50,361
If you really think they're
spies, we should be asking

25
00:00:50,481 --> 00:00:51,721
who's the spymaster.

26
00:00:51,841 --> 00:00:54,601
I'm really hard
to get rid of, Mr Barton.

27
00:00:55,601 --> 00:00:56,601
Are you?

28
00:01:02,001 --> 00:01:05,121
Should I say spy...Master?

29
00:01:05,241 --> 00:01:07,081
You can't be.

30
00:01:07,201 --> 00:01:08,881
Oh, I can be. I very much am.

31
00:01:12,201 --> 00:01:14,241
Everything that you think
you know...

32
00:01:14,361 --> 00:01:15,681
No, no, no, no, no.

33
00:01:15,801 --> 00:01:17,201
...Is a lie.

34
00:01:55,601 --> 00:01:57,481
DOCTOR: Hi, Doctor.

35
00:01:57,601 --> 00:02:00,481
Oh! Hi.

36
00:02:00,601 --> 00:02:01,761
How are you doing?

37
00:02:01,881 --> 00:02:02,801
Good.

38
00:02:02,921 --> 00:02:05,721
Just talking to myself
to prove I'm still alive.

39
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:08,401
I was wondering...

40
00:02:09,721 --> 00:02:12,441
...what would you say to
the others if they were here?

41
00:02:14,161 --> 00:02:16,401
"Don't panic.”

42
00:02:20,721 --> 00:02:22,321
Yaz! Hold on!

43
00:02:22,441 --> 00:02:25,241
(FRANTIC SHOUTING)

44
00:02:27,521 --> 00:02:29,201
What?

45
00:02:29,321 --> 00:02:30,281
DOCTOR: Of course,

46
00:02:30,401 --> 00:02:32,121
I'm usually saying it as much
to myself as I am to them.

47
00:02:32,241 --> 00:02:34,641
Always a good reminder
when you're alone...

48
00:02:35,641 --> 00:02:37,241
...in the unknown...

49
00:02:38,521 --> 00:02:40,881
...all hope lost.

50
00:02:41,001 --> 00:02:42,921
(SHOUTING)

51
00:02:45,641 --> 00:02:46,961
No way.

52
00:02:48,321 --> 00:02:50,881
- (SONIC BUZZES)
- Won't work in here.

53
00:02:51,001 --> 00:02:53,441
Why not? Could be a clue.
A clue to what?

54
00:02:54,921 --> 00:02:56,001
What...

55
00:02:57,001 --> 00:02:58,041
...was that?

56
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:02,441
Interesting. Useful. Maybe.

57
00:03:04,121 --> 00:03:05,961
Another! Even better.

58
00:03:06,081 --> 00:03:08,281
What are you?

59
00:03:08,401 --> 00:03:09,601
Pathways?

60
00:03:10,961 --> 00:03:12,361
Signals?

61
00:03:12,481 --> 00:03:13,601
Synapses?

62
00:03:13,721 --> 00:03:14,841
I could be inside something.

63
00:03:14,961 --> 00:03:17,921
Oh, I hope it's not a liver.
I hate being inside livers.

64
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:19,161
People always get so offended.

65
00:03:19,281 --> 00:03:20,561
"What are you doing
in my liver again?"

66
00:03:20,681 --> 00:03:21,681
WOMAN: Hello?

67
00:03:23,321 --> 00:03:25,481
DOCTOR: Hello?

68
00:03:25,601 --> 00:03:27,241
WOMAN: Hello?

69
00:03:29,761 --> 00:03:31,641
"4C seat pocket."

70
00:03:34,121 --> 00:03:35,561
No way.

71
00:03:35,681 --> 00:03:37,201
(GROANS)

72
00:03:37,321 --> 00:03:38,801
Hey! Hey!

73
00:03:38,921 --> 00:03:40,521
I've got a plan.

74
00:03:44,401 --> 00:03:45,881
Can you hear me?

75
00:03:46,001 --> 00:03:47,801
I'm trying to find you...
somehow.

76
00:03:49,721 --> 00:03:51,921
(DOCTOR CRIES OUT)

77
00:03:55,721 --> 00:03:57,641
Please be assured
all this will pass.

78
00:03:57,761 --> 00:04:00,281
I shall be recovered
momentarily.

79
00:04:00,401 --> 00:04:03,601
- "Open panel in floor"!
- What does it say next?

80
00:04:03,721 --> 00:04:06,361
"Connect the cable...

81
00:04:06,481 --> 00:04:07,481
"...to your phone."

82
00:04:07,601 --> 00:04:09,121
(STRAINS)

83
00:04:11,281 --> 00:04:12,721
Welcome aboard.

84
00:04:12,841 --> 00:04:16,161
You are kidding!
How's she doing that?!

85
00:04:16,281 --> 00:04:18,041
I realise you have questions.

86
00:04:18,161 --> 00:04:20,801
Where are you?!
We're going to die!

87
00:04:20,921 --> 00:04:23,561
First of all,
you're not going to die.

88
00:04:23,681 --> 00:04:25,681
Second of all
don't talk back to the screens.

89
00:04:25,801 --> 00:04:28,401
Obviously, I'm a recording
and I can't hear you.

90
00:04:28,521 --> 00:04:30,161
Third, don't panic.
Especially you, Graham.

91
00:04:30,281 --> 00:04:31,761
I'm not panicking!

92
00:04:31,881 --> 00:04:32,921
Yes, you were.

93
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:34,681
And I did just say don't
talk back to the screens.

94
00:04:34,801 --> 00:04:35,601
Eh?!

95
00:04:35,721 --> 00:04:37,961
Haven't got long. The bomb
in the cockpit knocked out

96
00:04:38,081 --> 00:04:40,401
the signals from the computer
to the engines.

97
00:04:40,521 --> 00:04:43,801
But the computers in this
aircraft aren't in the cockpit,

98
00:04:43,921 --> 00:04:45,601
they're under the cabin floor.

99
00:04:45,721 --> 00:04:47,121
Ryan, the app
should have opened.

100
00:04:47,241 --> 00:04:48,321
What app? Eh?

101
00:04:48,441 --> 00:04:50,121
How was this installed
on me phone?

102
00:04:51,521 --> 00:04:53,561
Use it to communicate
with the engines

103
00:04:53,681 --> 00:04:55,401
via the aircraft wiring.

104
00:04:55,521 --> 00:04:57,401
By the way, you have shut
the cockpit door, haven't you?

105
00:04:57,521 --> 00:04:58,561
That's vital.

106
00:04:58,681 --> 00:05:00,681
Cockpit doors are designed
to be incredibly robust,

107
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,161
I'L do it!

108
00:05:02,281 --> 00:05:04,401
Now pay attention.
Do this fast.

109
00:05:04,521 --> 00:05:05,681
I'm worried you might lose me
if there's a power surge.

110
00:05:05,801 --> 00:05:08,001
Lost her.

111
00:05:08,121 --> 00:05:09,601
Press the cursor up!

112
00:05:09,721 --> 00:05:11,481
We've got to stop this plane

113
00:05:11,601 --> 00:05:13,001
- from going down!
- Up, up, up!

114
00:05:14,281 --> 00:05:17,601
- Too many ups!
- Level out! Level out!

115
00:05:24,481 --> 00:05:25,721
When you say "recovered”,

116
00:05:25,841 --> 00:05:27,401
what do you mean?

117
00:05:27,521 --> 00:05:29,761
The paralysis will fade.

118
00:05:30,921 --> 00:05:32,361
You don't look paralysed.

119
00:05:32,481 --> 00:05:35,841
Not in this...realm
but in my earthly aspect.

120
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,521
Right.

121
00:05:38,521 --> 00:05:39,721
What's your name?

122
00:05:39,841 --> 00:05:41,201
I am Ada.

123
00:05:41,321 --> 00:05:42,761
And what do you think
this realm is, Ada?

124
00:05:42,881 --> 00:05:45,201
I...believe it to be my mind.

125
00:05:47,321 --> 00:05:49,641
Though I have not met
another here before.

126
00:05:49,761 --> 00:05:51,761
Then what do you think I am?

127
00:05:51,881 --> 00:05:54,921
I presume you are
a consequence of my thoughts.

128
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:57,481
No. I'm the Doctor,
and I'm very real.

129
00:05:57,601 --> 00:05:58,801
But you've been here before?

130
00:05:58,921 --> 00:06:01,481
Many times.
When the paralysis subsides,

131
00:06:01,601 --> 00:06:04,041
I find myself
fully back in my body,

132
00:06:04,161 --> 00:06:05,961
restored in the physical realm.

133
00:06:06,081 --> 00:06:08,001
If you are real, do you have
your own solution

134
00:06:08,121 --> 00:06:09,321
for egress from here?

135
00:06:09,441 --> 00:06:11,401
No exit strategy.

136
00:06:11,521 --> 00:06:13,281
(CRACKLING)

137
00:06:13,401 --> 00:06:15,601
Before I leave, I need to
work out what this place is.

138
00:06:16,641 --> 00:06:18,361
Oh!

139
00:06:20,441 --> 00:06:22,681
Those fragments of light...

140
00:06:22,801 --> 00:06:24,881
...or energy, why are they
surrounding you?

141
00:06:25,001 --> 00:06:27,201
They are always here with me.

142
00:06:27,321 --> 00:06:29,841
They place a word in my mind.

143
00:06:30,841 --> 00:06:32,041
"Kasaavin"?

144
00:06:43,001 --> 00:06:45,561
Ada...step away.

145
00:06:45,681 --> 00:06:48,281
Do not be afraid.

146
00:06:48,401 --> 00:06:50,481
This is my guardian.

147
00:06:50,601 --> 00:06:51,961
This is their realm!

148
00:06:53,601 --> 00:06:55,241
This is where they're from.

149
00:06:55,361 --> 00:06:57,361
But how did you bring us here?

150
00:06:59,241 --> 00:07:00,521
Unless...

151
00:07:01,601 --> 00:07:03,161
You can't be.

152
00:07:03,281 --> 00:07:05,121
But you must be.
What? Gateways?

153
00:07:05,241 --> 00:07:07,921
We go through you
and arrive in your realm?

154
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:11,761
And I say "realm” - it's not
a planet, not really a void.

155
00:07:11,881 --> 00:07:12,961
A separate dimension?

156
00:07:13,081 --> 00:07:14,321
Are we beyond our...

157
00:07:14,441 --> 00:07:15,521
...my universe?

158
00:07:17,401 --> 00:07:21,081
Little of what you are saying
makes sense to me,

159
00:07:21,201 --> 00:07:23,121
but I'm concerned
you'll be marooned here.

160
00:07:23,241 --> 00:07:24,681
When my guardian
has returned...

161
00:07:24,801 --> 00:07:27,361
- They're not your guardians.
- ...I can offer you my hand.

162
00:07:27,481 --> 00:07:29,401
We may leave this place
together.

163
00:07:30,961 --> 00:07:32,561
I don't think that will work.

164
00:07:32,681 --> 00:07:34,961
How will you know
if you do not try?

165
00:07:35,841 --> 00:07:37,601
Decide, Doctor.

166
00:07:43,761 --> 00:07:45,641
You got us level, Ryan.
Good lad!

167
00:07:45,761 --> 00:07:47,241
I can fly a plane!

168
00:07:47,361 --> 00:07:49,041
Can't ride a bike,
but I can fly a plane.

169
00:07:49,161 --> 00:07:50,561
Hey, look!

170
00:07:50,681 --> 00:07:52,361
Barton must have programmed in
a flight pattern

171
00:07:52,481 --> 00:07:53,681
before he left the cockpit.

172
00:07:53,801 --> 00:07:55,321
Looks like this app's
keying into it.

173
00:07:55,441 --> 00:07:57,721
- How did the Doctor do this?
- No idea.

174
00:07:57,841 --> 00:08:00,281
But now we've got to stay
on a plane without a cockpit...

175
00:08:01,281 --> 00:08:03,321
...till it decides
where to land.

176
00:08:06,881 --> 00:08:10,121
You should've seen me!
I was great!

177
00:08:10,241 --> 00:08:11,881
She did not have a clue.

178
00:08:12,001 --> 00:08:14,281
This'd better work.

179
00:08:14,401 --> 00:08:16,241
Final calibrations,

180
00:08:16,361 --> 00:08:18,201
and then we'll be ready.

181
00:08:19,601 --> 00:08:21,481
All our efforts
will come together

182
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,601
in a moment of beauty.

183
00:08:26,321 --> 00:08:28,041
We'll all have what we want.

184
00:08:28,161 --> 00:08:29,881
So you know, I don't appreciate

185
00:08:30,001 --> 00:08:33,801
last-minute changes of plan
as I'm about to take off.

186
00:08:35,841 --> 00:08:38,441
A little chaos
is a wonderful thing.

187
00:08:38,561 --> 00:08:40,721
Allowed me to swat those flies.

188
00:08:41,761 --> 00:08:43,841
(PHONE BEEPS)

189
00:08:46,241 --> 00:08:48,561
I've just been notified.

190
00:08:48,681 --> 00:08:51,001
My plane"s about to land
at its programmed destination.

191
00:08:51,121 --> 00:08:54,241
- They can't have survived.
- You told me

192
00:08:54,361 --> 00:08:57,281
everything was foolproof.
What's gone wrong?

193
00:08:57,401 --> 00:08:59,121
Watch your tone...

194
00:08:59,241 --> 00:09:01,161
...Mr Barton.

195
00:09:01,281 --> 00:09:03,241
I'm not your employee.

196
00:09:03,361 --> 00:09:05,641
(ALARM BLARES)

197
00:09:15,241 --> 00:09:17,121
How has she got there?

198
00:09:17,241 --> 00:09:19,241
What's happened?

199
00:09:21,841 --> 00:09:25,641
Nothing I can't deal with.
I'll drop you at your plane.

200
00:09:25,761 --> 00:09:28,881
You sort out her friends,
I'll deal with the Doctor.

201
00:09:37,161 --> 00:09:38,681
Ah.

202
00:09:38,801 --> 00:09:40,441
I'm getting...

203
00:09:40,561 --> 00:09:42,161
...19th century?

204
00:09:43,721 --> 00:09:45,121
Early...

205
00:09:46,121 --> 00:09:48,681
...with a touch of mid.

206
00:09:48,801 --> 00:09:50,521
Top notes...

207
00:09:50,641 --> 00:09:52,081
...London.

208
00:09:52,201 --> 00:09:53,601
Steam?

209
00:09:53,721 --> 00:09:55,081
Why am I getting steam?

210
00:09:55,201 --> 00:09:58,401
Nations shall cower in fear

211
00:09:58,521 --> 00:10:02,121
as my steam gun fires
1,000 bearings per minute.

212
00:10:02,241 --> 00:10:04,401
- (AUDIENCE GASPS)
- See the mouse survive

213
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:07,561
inside our revolutionary
diving bell!

214
00:10:07,681 --> 00:10:10,401
- (AUDIENCE GASPS)
- Touch the magneto.

215
00:10:10,521 --> 00:10:12,881
- Powerful shocks.
- (AUDIENCE GASPS)

216
00:10:13,001 --> 00:10:17,081
The perfect modern defence,
a grenade for the home.

217
00:10:17,201 --> 00:10:19,001
Intruders repelled with force.

218
00:10:19,121 --> 00:10:20,481
(AUDIENCE GASPS)

219
00:10:20,601 --> 00:10:22,041
It worked!

220
00:10:22,161 --> 00:10:23,161
Miss Gordon,

221
00:10:23,281 --> 00:10:24,881
- are you recovered?
-I am.

222
00:10:25,001 --> 00:10:26,521
- Thank you.
- Me too.

223
00:10:26,641 --> 00:10:27,561
Thanks for asking.

224
00:10:27,681 --> 00:10:28,921
Madam, this gallery

225
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:31,841
is full of
the extraordinary, but...

226
00:10:31,961 --> 00:10:34,201
...your apparition just now
was...

227
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:36,961
...impossible.
How did you do it?

228
00:10:38,841 --> 00:10:39,841
Er...

229
00:10:42,881 --> 00:10:45,601
I am bound never
to reveal my secrets.

230
00:10:45,721 --> 00:10:47,001
Go about your day,

231
00:10:47,121 --> 00:10:49,761
knowing that you may tell
people you were

232
00:10:49,881 --> 00:10:51,441
privileged to witness

233
00:10:51,561 --> 00:10:54,761
the Marvellous Apparating Man!

234
00:10:54,881 --> 00:10:57,561
Lady. Apparating Lady!

235
00:10:57,681 --> 00:11:00,081
- Every time!
- (APPLAUSE)

236
00:11:02,041 --> 00:11:05,441
The year, right now,
would be what?

237
00:11:05,561 --> 00:11:09,841
The year, madam,
remains 1834.

238
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:11,481
Yes.

239
00:11:14,161 --> 00:11:16,441
Marooned in the 19th century.

240
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:19,921
Hold on in there, fam.

241
00:11:22,481 --> 00:11:24,281
And there was no-one on board?

242
00:11:24,401 --> 00:11:28,561
No, sir. It appears the craft
landed itself via automation.

243
00:11:31,041 --> 00:11:34,801
Sir, we have had
this conversation before.

244
00:11:34,921 --> 00:11:37,361
If you're going to be testing
these sorts of systems,

245
00:11:37,481 --> 00:11:39,761
we really need to be
kept fully in the loop.

246
00:11:39,881 --> 00:11:42,121
I'm going to have to do
some tricky smoothing-over

247
00:11:42,241 --> 00:11:43,881
with the Civil Aviation
Authority.

248
00:11:45,721 --> 00:11:48,121
YAZ: How did he get here
so quick?

249
00:11:48,241 --> 00:11:49,561
I dunno.

250
00:11:49,681 --> 00:11:51,321
Where is "here", anyway?

251
00:11:51,441 --> 00:11:52,961
Britain.

252
00:11:53,081 --> 00:11:54,601
We're home.

253
00:11:54,721 --> 00:11:56,321
Almost.

254
00:11:56,441 --> 00:11:58,081
- Essex.
- Essex!

255
00:11:58,201 --> 00:12:00,681
That is my manor!
We are golden!

256
00:12:01,961 --> 00:12:03,641
What do we do, though?

257
00:12:04,681 --> 00:12:06,841
Figure out what Barton and O
are planning.

258
00:12:06,961 --> 00:12:08,081
That's what the Doctor
would do...

259
00:12:08,201 --> 00:12:10,721
- Yeah.
- ...if she was here.

260
00:12:10,841 --> 00:12:13,361
No, she'll be all right, Yaz.
Just got to believe.

261
00:12:13,481 --> 00:12:15,001
You didn't see that place.

262
00:12:15,121 --> 00:12:16,041
Eh?

263
00:12:16,161 --> 00:12:17,801
Still got access
to Barton's diary.

264
00:12:17,921 --> 00:12:20,521
He's giving a keynote speech
in London tomorrow night.

265
00:12:20,641 --> 00:12:22,401
That is where
we have got to get to.

266
00:12:22,521 --> 00:12:24,521
Yeah, without him
knowing we're still alive.

267
00:12:24,641 --> 00:12:27,001
So let's get moving.

268
00:12:29,601 --> 00:12:31,561
(KEYPAD BEEPS)

269
00:12:33,121 --> 00:12:35,081
I need tracking intel
on three people.

270
00:12:36,081 --> 00:12:37,281
As soon as you can!

271
00:12:38,721 --> 00:12:40,481
These are their names.

272
00:12:41,681 --> 00:12:43,361
ADA: Now we are safe,
Doctor, will you reveal

273
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:45,601
a little more concerning
how you came to be...

274
00:12:45,721 --> 00:12:46,641
- Agh!
- ...in that place

275
00:12:46,761 --> 00:12:48,641
and, indeed, who you are?

276
00:12:49,641 --> 00:12:51,721
I'm a traveller
in space and time.

277
00:12:51,841 --> 00:12:53,881
I was in the middle of dealing
with a planet-threatening

278
00:12:54,001 --> 00:12:56,881
conspiracy two centuries
from now, when I was attacked

279
00:12:57,001 --> 00:12:59,881
by an old enemy and exiled
to the place where I found you.

280
00:13:00,001 --> 00:13:02,081
- Oh!
- I'm not a fool, Doctor.

281
00:13:02,201 --> 00:13:03,881
And I'm not treating you
as one.

282
00:13:04,881 --> 00:13:06,241
This conspiracy involves

283
00:13:06,361 --> 00:13:08,881
those creatures you think
are your guardians.

284
00:13:09,001 --> 00:13:11,401
They're in alliance with
a renegade from my home planet

285
00:13:11,521 --> 00:13:13,841
and a 21st-century
tech inventor.

286
00:13:13,961 --> 00:13:17,161
186 years from now,
they're assassinating spies,

287
00:13:17,281 --> 00:13:19,241
and I am stuck here
without my TARDIS,

288
00:13:19,361 --> 00:13:21,361
and I need to find
my way back before...

289
00:13:21,481 --> 00:13:24,081
Ladies and gentlemen!

290
00:13:24,201 --> 00:13:27,761
See the incredible
shrinking device!

291
00:13:27,881 --> 00:13:29,721
Want to be smaller, ladies?

292
00:13:29,841 --> 00:13:31,281
You can!

293
00:13:31,401 --> 00:13:34,481
- (SCREAMING)
- Who's next? You, sir.

294
00:13:34,601 --> 00:13:36,881
Go, Ada. You too.

295
00:13:37,001 --> 00:13:38,281
Go!

296
00:13:38,401 --> 00:13:40,161
Ah, the happy couple!

297
00:13:41,681 --> 00:13:43,721
I said go!

298
00:13:43,841 --> 00:13:45,521
Do not move!

299
00:13:47,561 --> 00:13:49,161
Hands on heads.

300
00:13:50,841 --> 00:13:51,801
Hands on heads!

301
00:13:51,921 --> 00:13:53,161
(SCREAMING)

302
00:13:55,281 --> 00:13:56,321
Let them go...

303
00:13:57,641 --> 00:13:59,281
...and you can have me.

304
00:14:04,481 --> 00:14:06,001
I've got you anyway.

305
00:14:10,481 --> 00:14:12,121
Did you just move?

306
00:14:12,241 --> 00:14:14,401
- Did you move?
- No!

307
00:14:18,521 --> 00:14:20,241
(LAUGHS)

308
00:14:20,361 --> 00:14:22,721
Oh, my mistake.

309
00:14:22,841 --> 00:14:24,241
Sorry.

310
00:14:24,361 --> 00:14:25,801
Sorry.

311
00:14:27,041 --> 00:14:28,561
(SHRIEKING)

312
00:14:30,361 --> 00:14:31,761
When I kill them, Doctor,

313
00:14:31,881 --> 00:14:33,121
it gives me a little buzz.

314
00:14:34,801 --> 00:14:35,801
Right here.

315
00:14:35,921 --> 00:14:38,841
In the hearts. It's like...

316
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:40,961
How would I describe it?
It's like...

317
00:14:42,121 --> 00:14:43,881
It's like knowing
I'm in the right place,

318
00:14:44,001 --> 00:14:46,441
doing what I was made for.

319
00:14:47,681 --> 00:14:49,241
What do you want?

320
00:14:51,241 --> 00:14:52,681
Kneel.

321
00:14:56,761 --> 00:14:58,161
Kneel.

322
00:14:58,281 --> 00:15:00,401
Or they all die.

323
00:15:12,361 --> 00:15:15,001
Call me by my name.

324
00:15:21,521 --> 00:15:22,801
Master.

325
00:15:24,321 --> 00:15:25,401
Beg your pardon?

326
00:15:27,601 --> 00:15:28,841
Master!

327
00:15:28,961 --> 00:15:30,121
Can't hear you, love.

328
00:15:31,481 --> 00:15:32,761
Master.

329
00:15:40,081 --> 00:15:43,561
When I arrange for your death,
I expect you to stay dead.

330
00:15:46,441 --> 00:15:49,681
How did you escape?
How did you end up here?

331
00:15:54,321 --> 00:15:55,761
You don't know!

332
00:15:58,441 --> 00:16:02,241
You're not in control
of those creatures.

333
00:16:03,721 --> 00:16:05,921
I bet you don't even know
what they are.

334
00:16:07,081 --> 00:16:08,721
They're called the Kasaavin.

335
00:16:08,841 --> 00:16:10,681
And we have interests
in common.

336
00:16:10,801 --> 00:16:13,241
You, Barton...

337
00:16:13,361 --> 00:16:17,281
...and a race you barely know?
That's one uneasy alliance.

338
00:16:19,881 --> 00:16:21,241
Trust each other, do you?

339
00:16:21,361 --> 00:16:22,641
Oh, completely.

340
00:16:26,441 --> 00:16:28,881
By the way,
I bring news from home.

341
00:16:29,001 --> 00:16:30,641
Down, Doctor!

342
00:16:30,761 --> 00:16:32,721
(GUNFIRE)

343
00:16:32,841 --> 00:16:34,761
This is not designed for use

344
00:16:34,881 --> 00:16:36,001
- by a young lady!
- Nothing is.

345
00:16:36,121 --> 00:16:39,281
And yet I find myself
more than capable.

346
00:16:40,361 --> 00:16:41,361
All of you, out!

347
00:16:41,481 --> 00:16:43,641
Ada, I really do not approve!

348
00:16:43,761 --> 00:16:46,201
Run all you like, Doctor.

349
00:16:46,321 --> 00:16:47,761
You won't get far
without a TARDIS!

350
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:50,161
DOCTOR: Don't have a TARDIS.

351
00:16:55,241 --> 00:16:56,921
Do have an Ada.

352
00:16:57,201 --> 00:16:59,321
It's hard not to stand out
in this gear.

353
00:16:59,441 --> 00:17:00,761
- (PHONE RINGS)
- We've been on a night out.

354
00:17:00,881 --> 00:17:03,081
We're just coming home, that's
all. Nothing weird about that.

355
00:17:03,201 --> 00:17:06,081
- (PHONES RING)
- BARTON: Hello, friends.

356
00:17:06,201 --> 00:17:08,441
Or should I say
"plane thieves"?

357
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,961
What, did you think I wouldn't
be able to track you?

358
00:17:11,081 --> 00:17:14,041
We have your numbers, e-mails,
GPS. I even know how many

359
00:17:14,161 --> 00:17:17,201
more stamps you need for
a free coffee. So close, Ryan.

360
00:17:17,321 --> 00:17:19,441
Or should I say "Logan"?

361
00:17:19,561 --> 00:17:21,041
Look up.

362
00:17:21,161 --> 00:17:22,841
Your passports
have been revoked,

363
00:17:22,961 --> 00:17:24,281
your bank cards are frozen.

364
00:17:24,401 --> 00:17:26,401
We have a record of
everyone you know -

365
00:17:26,521 --> 00:17:28,241
friends, family, colleagues,

366
00:17:28,361 --> 00:17:30,721
everyone you ever followed
on social media.

367
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:31,881
Of course, we have

368
00:17:32,001 --> 00:17:34,001
cameras everywhere, and now
you're wanted for hijacking.

369
00:17:34,121 --> 00:17:37,201
Go on, go off-grid.
See how long you last.

370
00:17:40,001 --> 00:17:41,241
Hey, smash your phones now.

371
00:17:41,361 --> 00:17:44,081
Aw! Yasmin Khan
ls phoning her mum!

372
00:17:44,201 --> 00:17:45,641
- He don't half go on.
- MUM: Yaz?

373
00:17:45,761 --> 00:17:48,801
Hello. It's me. Listen, don't
listen to anything you hear.

374
00:17:50,081 --> 00:17:51,281
- Ryan!
- Did you not hear him?

375
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,521
We have to go dark.

376
00:17:53,641 --> 00:17:55,321
Run.

377
00:17:56,561 --> 00:17:58,761
MR BABBAGE: Surely we must
alert the authorities.

378
00:17:58,881 --> 00:18:00,441
DOCTOR: The authorities
won't be any help.

379
00:18:00,561 --> 00:18:03,041
ADA: Besides, what would
we tell them, Mr Babbage?

380
00:18:03,161 --> 00:18:04,481
I have no concept, Ada.

381
00:18:04,601 --> 00:18:07,681
I cannot explain any
of what I have seen today.

382
00:18:07,801 --> 00:18:10,401
Babbage? Charles Babbage?

383
00:18:10,521 --> 00:18:11,801
Yes.

384
00:18:11,921 --> 00:18:12,881
So this must be...

385
00:18:13,001 --> 00:18:14,601
- My Difference Engine.
- ...your Difference Engine!

386
00:18:14,721 --> 00:18:17,641
Oh. You...you know of it?

387
00:18:17,761 --> 00:18:20,481
- Er, just in passing.
- As yet unfinished.

388
00:18:20,601 --> 00:18:25,441
It will count and perform
quadratic equations.

389
00:18:25,561 --> 00:18:26,921
If you're Charles Babbage,

390
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:29,041
then you're not just
any old Ada.

391
00:18:29,161 --> 00:18:30,441
You're Ada Lovelace!

392
00:18:30,561 --> 00:18:32,961
Daughter of Lord Byron
and Annabella Milbanke,

393
00:18:33,081 --> 00:18:34,801
one of the great minds.

394
00:18:34,921 --> 00:18:37,481
I am Ada Gordon, madam.

395
00:18:37,601 --> 00:18:39,841
1834. Of course you are.

396
00:18:39,961 --> 00:18:42,201
Well, maybe one day, who knows,
you might meet a nice earl.

397
00:18:42,321 --> 00:18:44,321
This changes everything!

398
00:18:44,441 --> 00:18:46,121
This isn't an accident.

399
00:18:46,241 --> 00:18:48,081
Ada Lovelace
in Babbage's house?

400
00:18:48,201 --> 00:18:50,161
You're clues.

401
00:18:50,281 --> 00:18:52,121
- You're important.
-I'm...

402
00:18:52,241 --> 00:18:54,241
...delighted to hear it, madam.

403
00:18:54,361 --> 00:18:56,041
Yes, it's not good news.

404
00:18:56,161 --> 00:18:57,201
What's that?

405
00:18:57,321 --> 00:18:59,841
This is the Silver Lady...

406
00:19:00,841 --> 00:19:03,081
...a revolutionary
piece of engineering.

407
00:19:03,201 --> 00:19:05,321
But, like all great ladies,

408
00:19:05,441 --> 00:19:09,441
she is as much for decoration
as for purpose.

409
00:19:11,681 --> 00:19:13,841
- How did you come by this?
- It was a gift,

410
00:19:13,961 --> 00:19:15,081
delivered by a young man

411
00:19:15,201 --> 00:19:17,721
who said it was
a token of appreciation...

412
00:19:17,841 --> 00:19:19,121
...from his master.

413
00:19:21,001 --> 00:19:22,321
Was it?

414
00:19:24,081 --> 00:19:25,321
What does it do?

415
00:19:25,441 --> 00:19:26,921
It...moves...

416
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:29,001
...and, on occasion,

417
00:19:29,121 --> 00:19:30,881
- projects.
- On occasion

418
00:19:31,001 --> 00:19:32,601
projects something like this?

419
00:19:35,881 --> 00:19:38,321
M-Mr Babbage, you have seen
the same form.

420
00:19:38,441 --> 00:19:40,961
Madam, those are
my private notes.

421
00:19:42,081 --> 00:19:45,001
The Master and the Kasaavin,
what are they doing?

422
00:19:45,121 --> 00:19:47,801
Er... Do you understand her,
Miss Gordon?

423
00:19:47,921 --> 00:19:50,481
Not in the least, Mr Babbage.

424
00:19:50,601 --> 00:19:52,761
Ada, when was
your first paralysis?

425
00:19:52,881 --> 00:19:54,601
I was 13 years old.

426
00:19:54,721 --> 00:19:56,721
That is when I was first
transported to the place

427
00:19:56,841 --> 00:19:59,841
where we met
and I first saw an apparition.

428
00:19:59,961 --> 00:20:02,281
And over the years,
the paralysis recurs

429
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:03,481
with the same effect?

430
00:20:03,601 --> 00:20:07,561
Yes! No doctor has ever been
able to diagnose the cause.

431
00:20:07,681 --> 00:20:09,361
Well, this Doctor
may be able to.

432
00:20:09,481 --> 00:20:12,041
An apparition...
from this machine.

433
00:20:12,161 --> 00:20:13,281
- Correct.
- So,

434
00:20:13,401 --> 00:20:15,601
they take you, Ada,
multiple times...

435
00:20:16,561 --> 00:20:18,081
...from here and...

436
00:20:18,201 --> 00:20:19,721
...they study you
in their dimension,

437
00:20:19,841 --> 00:20:22,721
which means they can't be
in this dimension for long.

438
00:20:22,841 --> 00:20:25,361
But maybe they gain an ally,

439
00:20:25,481 --> 00:20:27,961
a mastermind who builds them

440
00:20:28,081 --> 00:20:32,601
a machine which
stabilises them in this world

441
00:20:32,721 --> 00:20:36,481
long enough for them to send
spies and to spread their work

442
00:20:36,601 --> 00:20:39,121
and start a plan.
Cos I've seen the map!

443
00:20:39,241 --> 00:20:41,601
In his hut. Multiple Earths.

444
00:20:41,721 --> 00:20:43,681
Except not.
Not multiple Earths.

445
00:20:44,921 --> 00:20:47,281
Multiple time periods.

446
00:20:47,401 --> 00:20:51,201
These creatures aren't just
alien spies on Earth,

447
00:20:51,321 --> 00:20:53,241
they're spies through time...

448
00:20:54,521 --> 00:20:56,401
...through history...

449
00:20:56,521 --> 00:20:58,001
- ...starting with you.
- (SONIC WHIRS)

450
00:20:58,121 --> 00:20:59,561
What are you doing?

451
00:20:59,681 --> 00:21:01,721
The man from the Adelaide
Gallery will be coming for me.

452
00:21:01,841 --> 00:21:02,841
I need to get back

453
00:21:02,961 --> 00:21:06,161
to where I came from, find
my friends and figure this out.

454
00:21:07,401 --> 00:21:09,401
And I've only got
one way out of here,

455
00:21:09,521 --> 00:21:11,241
the same way I came in.

456
00:21:11,361 --> 00:21:13,801
If I use my sonic on the Silver
Lady, I might be able to force

457
00:21:13,921 --> 00:21:16,601
this creature to throw me
back to the 21st century.

458
00:21:16,721 --> 00:21:18,561
- I hope.
- If this is your plan,

459
00:21:18,681 --> 00:21:20,001
it is fraught with risk.

460
00:21:20,121 --> 00:21:22,121
Where there's risk,
there's hope.

461
00:21:22,841 --> 00:21:24,281
Deep breath.

462
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:27,321
Ada, no!

463
00:21:34,961 --> 00:21:36,601
GRAHAM: No-one living here yet,

464
00:21:36,721 --> 00:21:38,521
no CCTV,
no neighbourhood watch.

465
00:21:40,761 --> 00:21:42,601
The one on the end. Go on!

466
00:21:48,401 --> 00:21:50,441
What if the Doctor
doesn't come back?

467
00:21:51,441 --> 00:21:53,481
What if we never see her again?

468
00:21:53,601 --> 00:21:55,441
We keep going...

469
00:21:55,561 --> 00:21:57,201
...stop Barton...

470
00:21:57,321 --> 00:22:00,121
...get rid of those creatures,
whatever they are.

471
00:22:00,241 --> 00:22:02,041
Ryan's right.

472
00:22:02,161 --> 00:22:05,441
We carry on doing what the Doc
would want us to do.

473
00:22:05,561 --> 00:22:07,681
I'm sorry, did you just say,
"Ryan's right"?

474
00:22:07,801 --> 00:22:10,481
Yes, I did!
Enjoy the moment, son.

475
00:22:10,601 --> 00:22:12,121
You won't hear it often.

476
00:22:14,881 --> 00:22:16,361
And that old guy...

477
00:22:18,081 --> 00:22:19,041
...if the Doctor knew him,

478
00:22:19,161 --> 00:22:21,281
how come she couldn't
recognise him?

479
00:22:23,801 --> 00:22:25,081
In the outback...

480
00:22:26,081 --> 00:22:28,761
...he said that he knew the Doc
when she was a man,

481
00:22:28,881 --> 00:22:30,721
and that first night we met...

482
00:22:31,801 --> 00:22:35,001
...she told me and Grace
that she'd been through, erm...

483
00:22:35,121 --> 00:22:36,801
...something called...

484
00:22:38,761 --> 00:22:40,761
...regeneration, like
her whole body had changed.

485
00:22:40,881 --> 00:22:43,241
We've spent all this time
with her

486
00:22:43,361 --> 00:22:44,801
and we don't even know
where she's from.

487
00:22:44,921 --> 00:22:48,121
Yeah, not for want of asking,
though. Eh? I mean!

488
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:50,001
And we will ask...

489
00:22:50,121 --> 00:22:51,321
...when we see her again...

490
00:22:52,561 --> 00:22:54,041
...which we will...

491
00:22:54,161 --> 00:22:57,361
...cos she is safe somewhere,
of course. Right?

492
00:22:58,881 --> 00:23:00,561
- Right.
- RYAN: Right.

493
00:23:04,641 --> 00:23:06,401
You know what she'd ask now?

494
00:23:07,841 --> 00:23:09,961
"What do we have
at our disposal?”

495
00:23:11,841 --> 00:23:13,161
Well...

496
00:23:13,281 --> 00:23:16,441
...I've, er...got to admit...

497
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:19,441
...] did keep a couple of
those spy gadgety things.

498
00:23:19,561 --> 00:23:21,361
Me too!

499
00:23:21,481 --> 00:23:22,681
Hey, are you

500
00:23:22,801 --> 00:23:25,241
- wearing the laser shoes?
- I might be.

501
00:23:25,361 --> 00:23:27,201
Why didn't you use them
on the plane?!

502
00:23:27,321 --> 00:23:29,401
What, in a confined space
like that?

503
00:23:29,521 --> 00:23:30,721
You're having a laugh,
ain't ya?

504
00:23:30,841 --> 00:23:32,121
That wouldn't have been
very smart, would it?

505
00:23:32,241 --> 00:23:34,321
And besides which, I forgot

506
00:23:34,441 --> 00:23:36,441
- to read the instructions.
- Graham!

507
00:23:36,561 --> 00:23:38,441
Well, we was in a rush!
What could I do?

508
00:23:39,481 --> 00:23:40,961
Rocket cuff links.

509
00:23:42,321 --> 00:23:44,681
To be fair, I didn't read the
instructions on those either.

510
00:23:44,801 --> 00:23:46,281
You doughnut!

511
00:23:46,401 --> 00:23:48,001
- BOTH: "Doughnut"?
- Yeah, the pair of you.

512
00:23:48,121 --> 00:23:49,681
Right couple of doughnuts!

513
00:23:51,281 --> 00:23:52,801
But...

514
00:23:52,921 --> 00:23:55,441
...there's no-one
I'd rather be on the run with.

515
00:24:01,801 --> 00:24:03,041
(CRUNCHING)

516
00:24:15,721 --> 00:24:16,881
What?

517
00:24:18,281 --> 00:24:19,241
No.

518
00:24:19,361 --> 00:24:20,761
(PLANE ROARS PAST)

519
00:24:20,881 --> 00:24:22,681
Ada! Are you OK?

520
00:24:22,801 --> 00:24:24,081
ADA: Are we safe?

521
00:24:25,201 --> 00:24:27,561
- (BOMBS AND GUNFIRE)
- WOMAN: Don't move.

522
00:24:28,761 --> 00:24:29,761
I said don't move!

523
00:24:29,881 --> 00:24:31,681
We're not hostile.
We're here by accident.

524
00:24:31,801 --> 00:24:34,441
What are you doing out here?
What are you wearing?

525
00:24:34,561 --> 00:24:36,881
(BOMB WHISTLES OVERHEAD
AND EXPLODES)

526
00:24:37,001 --> 00:24:38,041
ADA: What are those noises?

527
00:24:38,161 --> 00:24:40,521
Where are we? And when?

528
00:24:40,641 --> 00:24:41,761
Don't you know?

529
00:24:41,881 --> 00:24:44,241
Just landed. Concussion.
Humour me.

530
00:24:44,361 --> 00:24:47,041
Paris, 1943.

531
00:24:47,161 --> 00:24:48,401
(MAN SHOUTS)

532
00:24:48,521 --> 00:24:49,721
Oh, no!

533
00:24:50,801 --> 00:24:52,441
It's a patrol.

534
00:24:52,561 --> 00:24:56,041
Inside, quick.
We're not safe out here.

535
00:25:20,321 --> 00:25:22,201
I know you're here!

536
00:25:24,841 --> 00:25:26,521
I will find you!

537
00:25:34,161 --> 00:25:35,601
(BEEPING)

538
00:25:35,721 --> 00:25:37,521
Especially you, Doctor.

539
00:25:39,721 --> 00:25:42,161
Coming, ready or not.

540
00:25:49,801 --> 00:25:51,081
YAZ: Did you just hear
something?

541
00:25:53,121 --> 00:25:54,481
Ryan, come on!

542
00:25:57,161 --> 00:25:58,601
GRAHAM: Out this way.
Come on, out here!

543
00:25:58,721 --> 00:26:00,481
YAZ: Quick, quick!

544
00:26:00,601 --> 00:26:01,961
GRAHAM: Come on, quick!

545
00:26:03,601 --> 00:26:05,241
Come on, Yaz!

546
00:26:13,081 --> 00:26:14,961
- The shoe, Graham!
- What?

547
00:26:15,081 --> 00:26:18,041
Just stomp your foot,
or something!

548
00:26:18,161 --> 00:26:19,161
Again!

549
00:26:19,281 --> 00:26:21,041
You've got to aim better.

550
00:26:21,161 --> 00:26:23,761
What do you mean?
I didn't read the instructions!

551
00:26:23,881 --> 00:26:25,081
Dance, Graham, dance!

552
00:26:53,041 --> 00:26:54,881
Beautiful, isn't it?

553
00:26:56,561 --> 00:26:59,321
Dates back to the 19th century.

554
00:27:03,761 --> 00:27:06,281
What, not going
to say anything?

555
00:27:11,761 --> 00:27:15,201
This cannot still be about
me moving to the States.

556
00:27:15,321 --> 00:27:17,961
I text. I e-mail.

557
00:27:18,081 --> 00:27:20,881
I tried to friend you
on Facebook, and you refused.

558
00:27:21,001 --> 00:27:24,121
And trust me, I never use
Facebook unless forced.

559
00:27:25,161 --> 00:27:26,881
Why am I here?

560
00:27:30,361 --> 00:27:31,921
I'm in the country.

561
00:27:32,041 --> 00:27:34,241
I thought it would be nice
for us to see each other.

562
00:27:35,521 --> 00:27:39,081
- Thanks for coming.
- I didn't have a choice!

563
00:27:39,201 --> 00:27:42,001
I keep wondering,
does she know?

564
00:27:43,001 --> 00:27:44,281
Does she realise that I'm one

565
00:27:44,401 --> 00:27:47,241
of the most successful men
on the planet?

566
00:27:47,361 --> 00:27:50,321
I've changed the world.

567
00:27:51,641 --> 00:27:52,961
What do I have to do

568
00:27:53,081 --> 00:27:55,601
to get you to say, "Well done"?

569
00:27:58,881 --> 00:28:01,121
Well done.

570
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:05,121
Are we finished?

571
00:28:05,241 --> 00:28:06,681
No.

572
00:28:07,921 --> 00:28:09,641
I wanted to see you...

573
00:28:11,081 --> 00:28:12,721
...on the last day.

574
00:28:13,921 --> 00:28:15,721
On the what?

575
00:28:15,841 --> 00:28:18,601
So that you could be the first.

576
00:28:23,801 --> 00:28:25,761
(SCREAMS)

577
00:28:33,441 --> 00:28:34,921
(BANGING ON DOOR)

578
00:28:41,281 --> 00:28:42,281
Yes?

579
00:28:46,001 --> 00:28:48,041
(CLATTERING)

580
00:29:02,841 --> 00:29:04,001
You're new.

581
00:29:09,601 --> 00:29:10,681
(BREATHES RAPIDLY)

582
00:29:12,161 --> 00:29:14,441
(FLOORBOARDS CREAK)

583
00:29:27,081 --> 00:29:28,121
(THUDS CANE)

584
00:29:28,241 --> 00:29:29,401
(GUNFIRE)

585
00:29:37,281 --> 00:29:39,081
(GUNFIRE STOPS)

586
00:29:39,201 --> 00:29:40,681
(THUDS CANE)

587
00:29:59,321 --> 00:30:00,841
(DOOR CLOSES)

588
00:30:12,121 --> 00:30:14,761
You are a life-saver.

589
00:30:16,441 --> 00:30:18,961
Got some interesting stuff
under the floorboards here.

590
00:30:20,121 --> 00:30:22,881
Wireless radio equipment.

591
00:30:23,001 --> 00:30:26,321
As issued by the British
Special Operations Executive.

592
00:30:26,441 --> 00:30:29,241
Very distinct, very large
and very difficult

593
00:30:29,361 --> 00:30:30,801
to hide.

594
00:30:30,921 --> 00:30:32,681
You're not Parisian.
You're a British spy.

595
00:30:32,801 --> 00:30:34,161
I know that face.

596
00:30:34,281 --> 00:30:36,041
Code name Madeleine.
Real name

597
00:30:36,161 --> 00:30:38,361
Noor Inayat Khan.

598
00:30:38,481 --> 00:30:39,521
First female wireless operator

599
00:30:39,641 --> 00:30:43,081
to be dropped behind enemy
lines. Very nice to meet you.

600
00:30:43,201 --> 00:30:46,041
I'm not where I wanted to be,
but I can work with this.

601
00:30:46,161 --> 00:30:47,641
Ada, wait till you hear
about Noor.

602
00:30:47,761 --> 00:30:49,201
She's as impressive as you.

603
00:30:49,321 --> 00:30:50,361
You grabbing my hand must have

604
00:30:50,481 --> 00:30:52,761
thrown us off course,
spat us out here.

605
00:30:53,801 --> 00:30:55,881
I should like to come out
from the floor now.

606
00:30:56,001 --> 00:30:57,361
Oh!

607
00:30:58,721 --> 00:31:00,641
Who are you?

608
00:31:00,761 --> 00:31:02,761
How do you know
so much about me?

609
00:31:02,881 --> 00:31:05,401
And why are you both
wearing such strange clothes?

610
00:31:06,441 --> 00:31:09,441
That soldier's voice - he was
in the Adelaide Gallery.

611
00:31:09,561 --> 00:31:10,801
How can he be here?

612
00:31:10,921 --> 00:31:12,961
He's in league
with the Kasaavin,

613
00:31:13,081 --> 00:31:14,081
those creatures of light.

614
00:31:14,201 --> 00:31:16,281
I'd hoped to get back to their
home dimension, where we met,

615
00:31:16,401 --> 00:31:18,561
and then to the 21st century.

616
00:31:18,681 --> 00:31:20,561
But we ended up here
instead, which is,

617
00:31:20,681 --> 00:31:23,641
you know, 19th century
to 20th, it's progress.

618
00:31:23,761 --> 00:31:27,041
But the Master tracked me down,
and now he wants me dead,

619
00:31:27,161 --> 00:31:29,401
whereas I am a big fan
of being alive.

620
00:31:30,481 --> 00:31:32,681
Ada? Are you all right?

621
00:31:32,801 --> 00:31:34,761
(DISTANT GUNFIRE)

622
00:31:36,041 --> 00:31:38,361
I have always wanted
to return to Paris.

623
00:31:39,681 --> 00:31:41,521
NOOR: It's not at its best.

624
00:31:41,641 --> 00:31:44,001
Nightly bombing raids.

625
00:31:44,121 --> 00:31:46,361
Millions dead.

626
00:31:46,481 --> 00:31:49,041
They promised us
war at this scale would never

627
00:31:49,161 --> 00:31:52,241
happen again,
and yet here we are.

628
00:31:52,361 --> 00:31:54,761
This isn't the first time?

629
00:31:56,201 --> 00:31:57,601
Who are you people?

630
00:31:57,721 --> 00:32:00,321
We're your allies, I promise.

631
00:32:00,441 --> 00:32:02,561
This is the future.

632
00:32:02,681 --> 00:32:04,561
A world on fire.

633
00:32:04,681 --> 00:32:06,641
These are the dark times.

634
00:32:06,761 --> 00:32:08,561
But they don't sustain.

635
00:32:10,161 --> 00:32:12,361
Darkness never sustains...

636
00:32:13,761 --> 00:32:16,601
...even though sometimes
it feels like it might.

637
00:32:16,721 --> 00:32:19,641
I need to turn this
to our advantage

638
00:32:19,761 --> 00:32:21,761
and get the Master
off my trail.

639
00:32:21,881 --> 00:32:23,881
He's masquerading
as a German soldier.

640
00:32:24,001 --> 00:32:25,681
That's a low, even for him.

641
00:32:25,801 --> 00:32:28,001
Code name Madeleine, what
equipment do you have here?

642
00:32:28,121 --> 00:32:29,721
Only my radio equipment.

643
00:32:29,841 --> 00:32:32,641
No gun. No cyanide pill.
I'm a pacifist.

644
00:32:32,761 --> 00:32:35,601
Snap! Strong position
to take during wartime.

645
00:32:35,721 --> 00:32:36,721
Two pacifists

646
00:32:36,841 --> 00:32:38,961
and a 19th-century
descendant of Byron

647
00:32:39,081 --> 00:32:40,601
against the Nazis in Paris

648
00:32:40,721 --> 00:32:41,761
and an alien invasion

649
00:32:41,881 --> 00:32:44,481
across multiple dimensions.

650
00:32:44,601 --> 00:32:46,441
That's a big to-do list.

651
00:32:46,561 --> 00:32:48,241
(DOCTOR SIGHS)

652
00:32:50,921 --> 00:32:52,161
I have an idea!

653
00:32:52,281 --> 00:32:55,201
And you two brilliant people
are a big part of it.

654
00:32:56,881 --> 00:32:59,681
(RINGING TONE)

655
00:32:59,801 --> 00:33:01,521
Hello?

656
00:33:01,641 --> 00:33:02,881
Sonya, it's me.

657
00:33:03,001 --> 00:33:04,841
Where are you, idiot?

658
00:33:04,961 --> 00:33:06,721
What sort of trouble have you
gone and got yourself into?

659
00:33:06,841 --> 00:33:09,081
Shut up. I'm fine,
but I can't talk long.

660
00:33:09,201 --> 00:33:11,161
Tell Mum and Dad not to worry.

661
00:33:11,281 --> 00:33:12,921
SONYA: Oh, yeah,
cos that's going to work...

662
00:33:13,041 --> 00:33:15,201
Your name's all over the news.

663
00:33:15,321 --> 00:33:16,681
Have you gone rogue?

664
00:33:16,801 --> 00:33:19,361
Shut up and listen.
I'm with Graham and Ryan.

665
00:33:19,481 --> 00:33:21,401
We're fine. There's just been
a bit of a misunderstanding.

666
00:33:21,521 --> 00:33:23,281
If anyone comes to the door
and wants you to go with them,

667
00:33:23,401 --> 00:33:26,001
just refuse. Stay in the flat
and don't let anyone in.

668
00:33:27,441 --> 00:33:28,361
Keep yourself safe.

669
00:33:28,481 --> 00:33:31,881
I'm worried they'll come
for you. I've got to go.

670
00:33:35,521 --> 00:33:36,801
(TYRES SCREECH)

671
00:33:36,921 --> 00:33:39,201
Down! Get down!
Face down on the floor!

672
00:33:39,321 --> 00:33:40,401
All right, all right.

673
00:33:40,521 --> 00:33:44,041
Sorry, gents, it's you who's
getting down on the floor.

674
00:33:47,721 --> 00:33:51,361
This is the most advanced
laser shoe known to man.

675
00:33:52,761 --> 00:33:54,721
Ain't worth
the resistance, lads.

676
00:33:54,841 --> 00:33:56,841
Guns down and on the floor.

677
00:33:58,841 --> 00:34:01,401
Don't make me do
the ol' soft-shoe shuffle.

678
00:34:03,841 --> 00:34:05,441
Your boss thinks we're stupid.

679
00:34:05,561 --> 00:34:07,441
She made the call
knowing that you'd come for us.

680
00:34:07,561 --> 00:34:09,001
And now we're taking
your phones

681
00:34:09,121 --> 00:34:10,401
and we're going
to raid your GPS.

682
00:34:10,521 --> 00:34:12,761
How's that for smart?
(CHUCKLES)

683
00:34:12,881 --> 00:34:15,481
Ryan!
Don't tell them the plan!

684
00:34:15,601 --> 00:34:16,961
Oh, yeah.

685
00:34:17,081 --> 00:34:18,721
Sorry, I got a bit
carried away.

686
00:34:18,841 --> 00:34:21,081
- Come on, let's go.
- (ENGINE STARTS)

687
00:34:24,441 --> 00:34:25,801
(FOUR BEEPS)

688
00:34:25,921 --> 00:34:27,521
(FOUR BEEPS)

689
00:34:27,641 --> 00:34:28,801
(FOUR BEEPS)

690
00:34:35,521 --> 00:34:36,961
That's not a code.

691
00:34:37,081 --> 00:34:38,121
Not to you.

692
00:34:39,321 --> 00:34:40,601
If this works, I'm going

693
00:34:40,721 --> 00:34:42,961
to need you to find
something for me.

694
00:34:44,921 --> 00:34:47,241
This is a very personal code.

695
00:34:49,081 --> 00:34:50,681
(TWO SETS OF FOUR BEEPS)

696
00:34:50,801 --> 00:34:53,001
(TWO SETS OF FOUR BEEPS)

697
00:34:56,041 --> 00:34:57,961
The rhythm of two hearts.

698
00:35:02,121 --> 00:35:06,641
(BEEPS CONTINUE)

699
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:26,721
That got his attention.

700
00:35:28,201 --> 00:35:29,801
He's not so far.

701
00:35:30,961 --> 00:35:32,441
I can sense him.

702
00:35:34,281 --> 00:35:35,281
DOCTOR: Contact.

703
00:35:37,881 --> 00:35:39,921
O: Contact.

704
00:35:41,441 --> 00:35:43,401
O: Old-school.

705
00:35:43,521 --> 00:35:45,921
You're not the only one
who can do classic.

706
00:35:46,961 --> 00:35:49,241
So, how are you holding up

707
00:35:49,361 --> 00:35:52,161
without a TARDIS
or your friends

708
00:35:52,281 --> 00:35:54,281
or a hope...

709
00:35:55,321 --> 00:35:57,121
...a fugitive in time?

710
00:35:57,241 --> 00:35:58,841
All right.

711
00:35:58,961 --> 00:36:02,521
You've come all this way.
You've got me cornered.

712
00:36:04,241 --> 00:36:05,921
I'll meet you.

713
00:36:06,041 --> 00:36:07,681
No troops.

714
00:36:07,801 --> 00:36:09,441
No soldiers.

715
00:36:09,561 --> 00:36:11,241
Just us.

716
00:36:14,601 --> 00:36:16,041
Where?

717
00:36:16,161 --> 00:36:18,441
Where do you think?

718
00:36:18,561 --> 00:36:20,761
(AIR-RAID SIREN WAILS)

719
00:36:23,441 --> 00:36:26,041
(PLANE ROARS PAST)

720
00:36:30,401 --> 00:36:32,881
It's cold up here!

721
00:36:33,001 --> 00:36:34,281
(WIND HOWLS)

722
00:36:36,201 --> 00:36:37,601
It's worse than Jodrell Bank.

723
00:36:37,721 --> 00:36:39,961
Did I ever apologise for that?

724
00:36:40,081 --> 00:36:41,721
No.

725
00:36:41,841 --> 00:36:43,681
Good.

726
00:36:43,801 --> 00:36:45,201
How's the shoulder?

727
00:36:47,601 --> 00:36:48,521
Painful.

728
00:36:48,641 --> 00:36:50,081
I don't like
what you're wearing.

729
00:36:50,201 --> 00:36:51,601
Or the company you keep.

730
00:36:51,721 --> 00:36:53,321
How have you managed that?

731
00:36:53,441 --> 00:36:55,681
You're not exactly
their Aryan archetype.

732
00:36:55,801 --> 00:36:59,481
Tiny Teutonic
psychic perception filter.

733
00:36:59,601 --> 00:37:01,561
Learned it at school.

734
00:37:01,681 --> 00:37:04,201
Lets people see
what they want to see.

735
00:37:04,321 --> 00:37:06,281
I'm assuming it was you
who hijacked the MI6 car.

736
00:37:06,401 --> 00:37:07,321
That was fun.

737
00:37:07,441 --> 00:37:08,961
And assassinated C.

738
00:37:09,081 --> 00:37:10,761
Mandraffian laser rifle.

739
00:37:10,881 --> 00:37:12,281
One shot.

740
00:37:13,321 --> 00:37:15,161
I've still got an eye for it.

741
00:37:17,441 --> 00:37:18,681
Why were the Kasaavin

742
00:37:18,801 --> 00:37:20,361
assassinating spies?

743
00:37:23,041 --> 00:37:25,281
Earth's intelligence services

744
00:37:25,401 --> 00:37:27,561
started to realise
their presence.

745
00:37:27,681 --> 00:37:29,121
So, what, you brought
the Kasaavin to Earth?

746
00:37:29,241 --> 00:37:32,201
They were already here.
(CHUCKLES)

747
00:37:32,321 --> 00:37:34,601
I just persuaded them
we had interests in common.

748
00:37:34,721 --> 00:37:36,961
The Kasaavin are embedded
across the whole

749
00:37:37,081 --> 00:37:41,081
of this universe,
spies from another dimension.

750
00:37:41,201 --> 00:37:42,721
As I said to Mr Barton...

751
00:37:44,561 --> 00:37:46,041
...think of them as Russia...

752
00:37:47,481 --> 00:37:48,521
...but bigger.

753
00:37:48,641 --> 00:37:50,801
Sleeper agents everywhere,

754
00:37:50,921 --> 00:37:54,761
waiting to be activated,
amassing information

755
00:37:54,881 --> 00:37:57,081
in case they need to attack.

756
00:37:57,201 --> 00:38:01,601
And, I mean, you know me.
I can't help myself.

757
00:38:01,721 --> 00:38:03,721
I have to stick my oar in.

758
00:38:05,841 --> 00:38:07,561
What have you done?

759
00:38:09,481 --> 00:38:11,961
Suggested a better plan.

760
00:38:15,841 --> 00:38:17,521
(TYRES SCREECH)

761
00:38:19,241 --> 00:38:20,961
YAZ: Over here!

762
00:38:22,881 --> 00:38:23,961
Is she alive?

763
00:38:25,281 --> 00:38:26,721
No.

764
00:38:28,321 --> 00:38:30,041
What's she even doing here?

765
00:38:32,121 --> 00:38:33,601
Where's Barton?

766
00:38:33,721 --> 00:38:35,481
This is where his guys
were supposed to lead us,

767
00:38:35,601 --> 00:38:36,641
and he's not here.

768
00:38:36,761 --> 00:38:38,201
(BEEP)

769
00:38:38,321 --> 00:38:40,761
Well done
overpowering my people.

770
00:38:40,881 --> 00:38:43,601
But did you really think
they wouldn't tell me?

771
00:38:43,721 --> 00:38:45,841
I have a significant
announcement to make,

772
00:38:45,961 --> 00:38:48,481
and you, my friends,
are two steps behind.

773
00:38:48,601 --> 00:38:50,441
- As usual.
- YAZ: We know all about you.

774
00:38:50,561 --> 00:38:52,841
We know some of your DNA
isn't human.

775
00:38:54,241 --> 00:38:55,441
So what are you, part alien?

776
00:38:55,561 --> 00:38:58,321
You really don't understand
who I am.

777
00:38:58,441 --> 00:38:59,721
I build things.

778
00:38:59,841 --> 00:39:00,841
I test them.

779
00:39:00,961 --> 00:39:04,521
So I let them test
a tiny part of me.

780
00:39:04,641 --> 00:39:07,521
And now it's time
for the global roll-out.

781
00:39:07,641 --> 00:39:09,161
I'm proof of concept.

782
00:39:09,281 --> 00:39:11,921
What concept?
What did they try?

783
00:39:12,041 --> 00:39:14,681
Look after my mum.

784
00:39:17,121 --> 00:39:18,361
He killed his own mum.

785
00:39:19,921 --> 00:39:21,641
And left her here.

786
00:39:29,481 --> 00:39:32,361
That machine was
in Barton's office.

787
00:39:37,281 --> 00:39:38,841
What are you doing?

788
00:39:38,961 --> 00:39:41,561
Communicating a message
back to London,

789
00:39:41,681 --> 00:39:43,641
just as the Doctor asked.

790
00:39:43,761 --> 00:39:47,161
- Why are we trusting her?
- I have seen

791
00:39:47,281 --> 00:39:49,281
extraordinary things with her.

792
00:39:50,521 --> 00:39:54,921
She's wise and unafraid,
and I believe in her.

793
00:39:55,961 --> 00:39:59,481
W-What is this...contraption
she's left us with?

794
00:40:00,681 --> 00:40:04,201
I don't know. I've never seen
anything like that before.

795
00:40:05,441 --> 00:40:06,681
So...

796
00:40:06,801 --> 00:40:08,921
...are you ready
to brave the night?

797
00:40:10,681 --> 00:40:13,921
(DISTANT GUNFIRE
AND EXPLOSIONS)

798
00:40:27,681 --> 00:40:29,361
How does that fit here?

799
00:40:30,601 --> 00:40:33,441
She did say,
"Look for something anomalous."

800
00:40:35,721 --> 00:40:37,961
Use...the device.

801
00:40:41,481 --> 00:40:43,361
(PHONE JINGLES)

802
00:40:47,601 --> 00:40:49,321
(DIALLING)

803
00:40:49,441 --> 00:40:50,441
(RINGING TONE)

804
00:40:50,561 --> 00:40:53,281
- (PHONE RINGS)
- Oh! Must change the ringtone.

805
00:40:53,401 --> 00:40:55,481
Sent it to voicemail.

806
00:40:55,601 --> 00:40:57,081
Probably just asking
if I've had an accident

807
00:40:57,201 --> 00:40:58,441
in the last five years.

808
00:40:58,561 --> 00:41:00,321
They hate it when you give them
a list, though, don't they?

809
00:41:00,441 --> 00:41:03,041
Why didn't you die when
the Kasaavin attacked you?

810
00:41:03,161 --> 00:41:06,281
Me and Yaz,
both time travellers,

811
00:41:06,401 --> 00:41:08,481
fizzing with artron energy,

812
00:41:08,601 --> 00:41:10,681
and my DNA not matching
the rest of humanity,

813
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:11,801
we confused them.

814
00:41:11,921 --> 00:41:13,161
And I don't think
they're as stable

815
00:41:13,281 --> 00:41:15,641
in this dimension
as they'd like to be.

816
00:41:15,761 --> 00:41:17,601
What deal have you made
with them?

817
00:41:17,721 --> 00:41:20,521
I showed them and Barton
what was possible.

818
00:41:21,521 --> 00:41:22,521
They helped me
lay a trap for you,

819
00:41:22,641 --> 00:41:24,681
and I raised their ambitions.

820
00:41:27,561 --> 00:41:29,281
Of course, ultimately...

821
00:41:29,401 --> 00:41:32,641
...the Kasaavin are just
the mechanism.

822
00:41:32,761 --> 00:41:35,761
They... They don't have
my vision. You know?

823
00:41:35,881 --> 00:41:37,361
And what vision is that?

824
00:41:37,481 --> 00:41:39,161
Maximum carnage.

825
00:41:39,281 --> 00:41:40,441
I don't understand.

826
00:41:40,561 --> 00:41:41,921
No, no, I know you don't.

827
00:41:42,921 --> 00:41:44,321
But you will.

828
00:41:44,441 --> 00:41:47,201
And of course,
the best thing is...

829
00:41:48,241 --> 00:41:50,361
...everyone loses except me.

830
00:41:50,481 --> 00:41:53,081
Barton and those creatures
do the dirty work,

831
00:41:53,201 --> 00:41:54,801
and once they're done,
I get rid of them,

832
00:41:54,921 --> 00:41:57,281
having destroyed your precious
human race in the process.

833
00:41:57,401 --> 00:41:58,841
Win-win-win.

834
00:41:58,961 --> 00:42:01,481
When does all this stop
for you?

835
00:42:02,481 --> 00:42:04,001
The games?

836
00:42:04,121 --> 00:42:05,321
The betrayals?

837
00:42:05,441 --> 00:42:06,641
The killing?

838
00:42:06,761 --> 00:42:08,761
Why would it stop?

839
00:42:08,881 --> 00:42:11,481
I mean, how else
would I get your attention?

840
00:42:12,881 --> 00:42:15,761
When did you last go home?

841
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:17,241
What do you mean?

842
00:42:19,561 --> 00:42:21,521
I took a trip home.

843
00:42:21,641 --> 00:42:24,241
To Gallifrey.

844
00:42:24,361 --> 00:42:27,721
Hiding in its little
bubble universe.

845
00:42:27,841 --> 00:42:30,161
Not sure how to describe
what I found.

846
00:42:30,281 --> 00:42:32,681
"Pulverised"?

847
00:42:32,801 --> 00:42:34,721
"Burned"?

848
00:42:34,841 --> 00:42:36,441
"Nuked"?

849
00:42:36,561 --> 00:42:39,121
All of the above.

850
00:42:40,481 --> 00:42:42,361
Someone destroyed it.

851
00:42:44,441 --> 00:42:46,281
Our home...

852
00:42:47,801 --> 00:42:49,441
...razed to the ground.

853
00:42:50,961 --> 00:42:52,561
Everyone killed.

854
00:42:54,201 --> 00:42:55,641
Everything burned.

855
00:42:59,321 --> 00:43:00,601
You're lying.

856
00:43:00,721 --> 00:43:03,481
You should really take a look.

857
00:43:03,601 --> 00:43:05,161
Oh, wait, you won't be able to.

858
00:43:05,281 --> 00:43:07,081
I just thought
I'd let you know before I...

859
00:43:07,201 --> 00:43:09,761
- (MEN SHOUT)
- Can you hear voices?

860
00:43:09,881 --> 00:43:12,241
Why are there troops
coming up the stairs?!

861
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:14,601
Oh. That's me...

862
00:43:14,721 --> 00:43:16,841
...and one of Blighty's
bravest radio operators.

863
00:43:16,961 --> 00:43:18,161
Very good at sending messages,

864
00:43:18,281 --> 00:43:21,761
particularly fake ones
designed to be intercepted.

865
00:43:21,881 --> 00:43:23,161
Now, finish
what you were saying!

866
00:43:23,281 --> 00:43:24,961
What have you done?!

867
00:43:25,081 --> 00:43:28,161
Sent a message to the Brits...

868
00:43:28,281 --> 00:43:31,241
...telling them how valuable
you've been...

869
00:43:31,361 --> 00:43:33,321
...as a double agent...

870
00:43:34,721 --> 00:43:38,161
...sending Nazi information
to the British.

871
00:43:40,561 --> 00:43:41,601
Facial perception filter?

872
00:43:41,721 --> 00:43:43,121
Very easy to jam.

873
00:43:43,241 --> 00:43:45,761
Now they'll see the real you.

874
00:43:45,881 --> 00:43:47,161
- Good luck.
- (LIFT BELL PINGS)

875
00:43:49,121 --> 00:43:51,961
(SOLDIERS SHOUT)

876
00:43:52,081 --> 00:43:54,001
I believe there's been
a misunderstanding.

877
00:43:54,121 --> 00:43:56,441
Can we talk about this?

878
00:43:56,561 --> 00:43:58,841
You've always struck me
as such reasonable people.

879
00:44:08,121 --> 00:44:10,041
(CHATTER)

880
00:44:12,761 --> 00:44:15,121
(PANTS HEAVILY)

881
00:44:15,241 --> 00:44:17,121
NOOR: Over here.

882
00:44:18,161 --> 00:44:19,401
Is this what you meant?

883
00:44:19,521 --> 00:44:21,481
That wasn't here last week.

884
00:44:21,601 --> 00:44:24,241
I bet it wasn't! So arrogant...

885
00:44:25,721 --> 00:44:27,881
...didn't even change
the appearance.

886
00:44:29,521 --> 00:44:32,561
OK, you two,
my best secret agents,

887
00:44:32,681 --> 00:44:34,521
time to go lock-picking.

888
00:44:37,841 --> 00:44:39,481
Why is this house so important?

889
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:40,641
This is not a house.

890
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:41,761
It's a machine

891
00:44:41,881 --> 00:44:44,201
that travels in space and time.

892
00:44:44,321 --> 00:44:45,641
This is my way back

893
00:44:45,761 --> 00:44:47,921
to finding my friends
and saving humanity.

894
00:44:48,041 --> 00:44:51,001
I know you think I'm mad,
but give me five minutes

895
00:44:51,121 --> 00:44:52,881
and you'll think
I'm the sanest person alive.

896
00:44:53,001 --> 00:44:54,241
OK, that was an overstatement.

897
00:44:54,361 --> 00:44:56,041
I said the Master's arrogant,

898
00:44:56,161 --> 00:44:57,281
but arrogance...

899
00:44:57,401 --> 00:44:58,921
...can trip you up.

900
00:45:00,641 --> 00:45:02,441
I know what this is!

901
00:45:02,561 --> 00:45:05,841
A temporal map, showing
every significant person

902
00:45:05,961 --> 00:45:08,881
in the development of computers
through history,

903
00:45:09,001 --> 00:45:10,921
starting with you, Ada.

904
00:45:11,041 --> 00:45:12,321
This is the plan!

905
00:45:12,441 --> 00:45:13,681
See?

906
00:45:13,801 --> 00:45:14,721
BOTH: No.

907
00:45:14,841 --> 00:45:17,081
W-What is a computer?

908
00:45:17,201 --> 00:45:19,161
Oh. Forget you heard that word.

909
00:45:19,281 --> 00:45:21,961
Otherwise I've just disrupted
the whole of history. Again.

910
00:45:22,081 --> 00:45:23,041
OK...

911
00:45:23,161 --> 00:45:25,441
Ah, my brain's fizzing. Good.

912
00:45:25,561 --> 00:45:29,041
The Kasaavin posted an agent
on every person on that map,

913
00:45:29,161 --> 00:45:32,121
because that's what spies do,
what Barton does.

914
00:45:32,241 --> 00:45:34,201
They gather all the data!

915
00:45:34,321 --> 00:45:37,121
Where does the DNA fit in?

916
00:45:37,241 --> 00:45:38,761
Kasaavin...

917
00:45:38,881 --> 00:45:40,601
...technology, DNA...

918
00:45:41,801 --> 00:45:43,561
How are they all connected?

919
00:45:43,681 --> 00:45:45,361
Oh!

920
00:45:45,481 --> 00:45:48,241
Human DNA.
That's what they were testing.

921
00:45:48,361 --> 00:45:51,201
How much of that
did you understand?

922
00:45:55,121 --> 00:45:56,441
Thank you.

923
00:45:57,801 --> 00:46:00,761
Today, I'm here to say
thank you

924
00:46:00,881 --> 00:46:03,241
to those of you
all around the world

925
00:46:03,361 --> 00:46:05,961
who've made our achievements
possible,

926
00:46:06,081 --> 00:46:08,201
to everyone who,
over the years,

927
00:46:08,321 --> 00:46:10,721
has given us everything.

928
00:46:10,841 --> 00:46:15,121
We gave you pieces of plastic
and circuitry and games...

929
00:46:15,241 --> 00:46:18,841
...and you handed us -
me, my company -

930
00:46:18,961 --> 00:46:21,761
total access to your lives -

931
00:46:21,881 --> 00:46:24,721
what you buy, where you go,

932
00:46:24,841 --> 00:46:27,641
who you text, what you text,

933
00:46:27,761 --> 00:46:32,921
every thought and photo and
post, every credit-card number,

934
00:46:33,041 --> 00:46:36,041
every birthday,
every memorable place

935
00:46:36,161 --> 00:46:38,681
and all your mothers'
maiden names.

936
00:46:38,801 --> 00:46:43,161
So thank you for carrying
our cameras in your pockets

937
00:46:43,281 --> 00:46:46,041
and putting our microphones
in your bedrooms,

938
00:46:46,161 --> 00:46:50,361
for signing up your kids,
handing them our devices.

939
00:46:50,481 --> 00:46:53,001
We told you, "Of course
your lives are private,

940
00:46:53,121 --> 00:46:55,441
"of course your data's safe.”

941
00:46:55,561 --> 00:46:58,041
And you believed us.

942
00:46:58,161 --> 00:47:01,281
You kept clicking "agree".

943
00:47:01,401 --> 00:47:02,881
And now...

944
00:47:03,001 --> 00:47:05,401
...we can do anything.

945
00:47:05,521 --> 00:47:09,361
I can send a text
to every device on this planet.

946
00:47:10,401 --> 00:47:11,921
(PHONE CHIMES)

947
00:47:12,041 --> 00:47:13,041
(PHONE CHIMES)

948
00:47:14,441 --> 00:47:15,441
(PHONE CHIMES)

949
00:47:18,121 --> 00:47:19,881
(PHONES CHIME)

950
00:47:23,961 --> 00:47:25,841
Go ahead.

951
00:47:25,961 --> 00:47:27,761
Read it.

952
00:47:27,881 --> 00:47:30,161
YAZ: "Humanity is over.

953
00:47:30,281 --> 00:47:32,761
"You have three minutes
to prepare.”

954
00:47:34,081 --> 00:47:35,361
Prepare for what?

955
00:47:36,881 --> 00:47:39,161
(MURMURING AND LAUGHTER)

956
00:47:39,281 --> 00:47:40,521
Funny, right?

957
00:47:41,601 --> 00:47:42,561
Except...

958
00:47:42,681 --> 00:47:44,161
...not a joke.

959
00:47:45,201 --> 00:47:49,281
We are way past peak human.

960
00:47:49,401 --> 00:47:51,801
We've created systems
that are smarter

961
00:47:51,921 --> 00:47:54,081
and can run more efficiently
than we do.

962
00:47:55,081 --> 00:47:56,601
So what's our purpose?

963
00:47:57,601 --> 00:47:59,561
We must be useful
for something.

964
00:48:00,561 --> 00:48:02,281
Well, the data tells us we are.

965
00:48:03,321 --> 00:48:05,281
We can repurpose.

966
00:48:05,401 --> 00:48:06,521
Well...

967
00:48:06,641 --> 00:48:08,241
...you all can.

968
00:48:10,361 --> 00:48:12,001
You know
the most efficient type

969
00:48:12,121 --> 00:48:14,241
of hard drives on planet Earth?

970
00:48:16,481 --> 00:48:17,561
Humans.

971
00:48:18,921 --> 00:48:22,321
Human DNA can store
so much data.

972
00:48:22,441 --> 00:48:24,761
We're the perfect
storage system,

973
00:48:24,881 --> 00:48:27,321
which means there are
over seven billion

974
00:48:27,441 --> 00:48:30,481
potentially incredibly useful
hard drives on this planet.

975
00:48:30,601 --> 00:48:36,441
All that's needed is to
reformat the whole of humanity.

976
00:48:38,881 --> 00:48:41,681
Luckily,
there's an app for that.

977
00:48:48,881 --> 00:48:50,081
Anyone feel like this is

978
00:48:50,201 --> 00:48:51,921
something we should be
worried about?

979
00:49:04,321 --> 00:49:05,561
Mum?

980
00:49:05,681 --> 00:49:07,521
I can't move!

981
00:49:09,441 --> 00:49:13,201
A handful of us will remain
sentient in order to supervise,

982
00:49:13,321 --> 00:49:14,561
maybe even rebuild.

983
00:49:14,681 --> 00:49:16,841
But for the rest of you...

984
00:49:17,921 --> 00:49:20,281
...welcome to
the end of your lives.

985
00:49:21,601 --> 00:49:23,121
Use your shoe on the machine.

986
00:49:24,721 --> 00:49:25,801
It doesn't make any difference.

987
00:49:25,921 --> 00:49:27,361
Cuff links!

988
00:49:29,561 --> 00:49:30,561
Move away.

989
00:49:31,881 --> 00:49:33,161
Now!

990
00:49:35,601 --> 00:49:36,521
I've just had

991
00:49:36,641 --> 00:49:41,001
the most infuriating 77 years
of my life.

992
00:49:41,121 --> 00:49:42,241
Have you any idea
how hard it is

993
00:49:42,361 --> 00:49:44,641
to live through
the 20th century?

994
00:49:46,201 --> 00:49:48,721
The places I've escaped from...

995
00:49:48,841 --> 00:49:52,441
(INHALES DEEPLY) Still...
just in time to...

996
00:49:52,561 --> 00:49:53,961
...watch you all pay.

997
00:49:54,081 --> 00:49:55,361
What's the machine?

998
00:49:58,881 --> 00:50:01,521
Conversion and transmission.

999
00:50:01,641 --> 00:50:02,881
We're transmitting

1000
00:50:03,001 --> 00:50:05,801
Kasaavin energy
around the world all at once

1001
00:50:05,921 --> 00:50:09,641
into every device,
hitting every human being

1002
00:50:09,761 --> 00:50:13,561
and erasing all their DNA
simultaneously.

1003
00:50:14,401 --> 00:50:16,601
- Yaz!
- I can't let go of it.

1004
00:50:20,001 --> 00:50:21,761
First her. Then you.

1005
00:50:23,921 --> 00:50:25,201
Then you.

1006
00:50:29,721 --> 00:50:31,001
Don't do this.

1007
00:50:33,241 --> 00:50:34,841
(MURMURING)

1008
00:50:34,961 --> 00:50:36,561
Extraction team in.

1009
00:50:36,681 --> 00:50:37,761
Immediately!

1010
00:50:46,561 --> 00:50:48,961
Sorry. I think
that might have been me.

1011
00:50:49,081 --> 00:50:51,761
And I'll admit, it was close.

1012
00:50:55,361 --> 00:50:56,801
What was that?

1013
00:50:56,921 --> 00:50:58,721
What do I keep telling you?

1014
00:50:58,841 --> 00:51:00,881
Conspiracy!

1015
00:51:02,161 --> 00:51:04,001
- No.
- Two can play

1016
00:51:04,121 --> 00:51:06,081
at embedding things in history.

1017
00:51:06,201 --> 00:51:08,561
I knew the Silver Lady
was important

1018
00:51:08,681 --> 00:51:10,281
and that you built it
for a reason.

1019
00:51:10,401 --> 00:51:11,881
But I couldn't work out why.

1020
00:51:13,441 --> 00:51:16,921
So I traced its movements
through history.

1021
00:51:17,041 --> 00:51:19,001
And when I saw that
Barton now owned it,

1022
00:51:19,121 --> 00:51:20,801
we stopped by his office.

1023
00:51:20,921 --> 00:51:22,321
Middle of last year,

1024
00:51:22,441 --> 00:51:24,081
using your TARDIS, I built

1025
00:51:24,201 --> 00:51:27,121
a fail-safe into that machine,
planted a virus.

1026
00:51:27,241 --> 00:51:28,681
If it ever detected

1027
00:51:28,801 --> 00:51:31,561
the massing of a Kasaavin army
within its systems -

1028
00:51:31,681 --> 00:51:33,481
total shutdown.

1029
00:51:36,641 --> 00:51:40,081
You're going to have to explain
yourself to them, Doctor.

1030
00:51:40,201 --> 00:51:42,081
Am I?

1031
00:51:43,641 --> 00:51:44,561
Listen, you lot,

1032
00:51:44,681 --> 00:51:45,881
I've rigged the Silver Lady

1033
00:51:46,001 --> 00:51:48,481
to exile you back
to your own dimension.

1034
00:51:48,601 --> 00:51:50,321
This planet's off-limits.

1035
00:51:50,441 --> 00:51:52,721
Oh, and you know that deal
he made with you?

1036
00:51:52,841 --> 00:51:55,041
O: Barton and these creatures
do the dirty work,

1037
00:51:55,161 --> 00:51:56,681
and once they're done,
I get rid of them,

1038
00:51:56,801 --> 00:51:59,441
having destroyed your precious
human race in the process.

1039
00:51:59,561 --> 00:52:01,161
Win-win-win.

1040
00:52:01,281 --> 00:52:03,481
Oh...

1041
00:52:03,601 --> 00:52:05,041
That's your name.

1042
00:52:05,161 --> 00:52:06,601
Don't wear it out.

1043
00:52:06,721 --> 00:52:08,841
That's the trouble
with modern technology.

1044
00:52:08,961 --> 00:52:11,041
You never know
when you're being spied upon.

1045
00:52:11,161 --> 00:52:13,121
(KASAAVIN MURMUR THREATENINGLY)

1046
00:52:13,241 --> 00:52:16,161
Don't... Don't listen to her.

1047
00:52:27,641 --> 00:52:28,641
No.

1048
00:52:29,961 --> 00:52:31,161
Doctor...

1049
00:52:33,401 --> 00:52:38,121
Doctor!

1050
00:52:39,561 --> 00:52:41,241
What?

1051
00:52:41,361 --> 00:52:43,761
You have a lot of
explaining to do.

1052
00:52:43,881 --> 00:52:45,921
- Like what?
- Like...

1053
00:52:46,041 --> 00:52:47,241
Who are they?

1054
00:52:47,361 --> 00:52:49,441
And are we being replaced?

1055
00:52:49,561 --> 00:52:50,681
No!

1056
00:52:50,801 --> 00:52:53,121
This is Ada, this is Noor.

1057
00:52:53,241 --> 00:52:54,441
1834,

1058
00:52:54,561 --> 00:52:58,361
1943. They helped me out. I'm
dropping them back in a sec.

1059
00:52:58,481 --> 00:53:00,561
How did you manage
to save our lives on the plane?

1060
00:53:00,681 --> 00:53:02,281
The plane!

1061
00:53:02,401 --> 00:53:04,401
Oh! I forgot!

1062
00:53:04,521 --> 00:53:05,921
Come on!

1063
00:53:07,881 --> 00:53:09,961
You have shut the cockpit
doors, haven't you?

1064
00:53:10,081 --> 00:53:11,041
That's vital.

1065
00:53:11,161 --> 00:53:13,281
Cockpit doors are designed
to be incredibly robust.

1066
00:53:17,801 --> 00:53:19,241
I love a laminator.

1067
00:53:20,561 --> 00:53:22,881
Stick these in Barton's
plane as it's being built

1068
00:53:23,001 --> 00:53:24,441
then reclaim my own TARDIS.

1069
00:53:25,481 --> 00:53:27,601
This is where I leave you.

1070
00:53:28,641 --> 00:53:30,281
Answer me one question.

1071
00:53:30,401 --> 00:53:33,321
The fascists - do they win?

1072
00:53:33,441 --> 00:53:34,641
Never.

1073
00:53:35,721 --> 00:53:37,481
Not while there's people
like you.

1074
00:53:39,401 --> 00:53:40,641
It's all right.

1075
00:53:40,761 --> 00:53:43,281
I'm just removing me
from your mind.

1076
00:53:50,801 --> 00:53:52,641
Boone chance.

1077
00:53:57,801 --> 00:53:59,521
(VWORPING)

1078
00:54:06,441 --> 00:54:09,001
Doctor? Does this
have to be the end?

1079
00:54:09,121 --> 00:54:14,961
All the things I've learned,
the advances, the machines!

1080
00:54:15,081 --> 00:54:17,361
I would dearly love
to see more.

1081
00:54:17,481 --> 00:54:19,761
I'm afraid I need to do
something about that.

1082
00:54:19,881 --> 00:54:21,681
- What do you mean?
- I'm ever so sorry, Ada.

1083
00:54:21,801 --> 00:54:23,521
D-Doctor, what are you doing?

1084
00:54:23,641 --> 00:54:25,521
Wiping the things you shouldn't
have knowledge of.

1085
00:54:25,641 --> 00:54:26,761
Including me.

1086
00:54:26,881 --> 00:54:28,161
But I want that knowledge.

1087
00:54:28,281 --> 00:54:30,241
Don't take it away.
Please don't take it a...

1088
00:54:32,281 --> 00:54:33,761
Oh, Ada.

1089
00:54:33,881 --> 00:54:35,921
You don't need a preview.

1090
00:54:36,041 --> 00:54:37,761
You'll figure it out
before anyone.

1091
00:54:37,881 --> 00:54:41,161
The first to see the potential
in things like that,

1092
00:54:41,281 --> 00:54:43,121
to work out what could be...

1093
00:54:44,121 --> 00:54:45,921
...what they can really do.

1094
00:54:46,041 --> 00:54:48,161
Computers start with you.

1095
00:54:49,961 --> 00:54:51,761
Sweet dreams, Ada Lovelace.

1096
00:55:01,481 --> 00:55:02,881
(VWORPING)

1097
00:55:12,001 --> 00:55:14,081
0. When did you last go home?

1098
00:55:14,201 --> 00:55:16,401
You should really take a look.

1099
00:56:11,121 --> 00:56:13,961
(JINGLING)

1100
00:56:18,441 --> 00:56:19,921
O: Geo-activated.

1101
00:56:26,521 --> 00:56:28,601
If you're seeing this...

1102
00:56:28,721 --> 00:56:31,081
...you've been to Gallifrey.

1103
00:56:33,961 --> 00:56:36,521
When I said someone did that..

1104
00:56:37,521 --> 00:56:39,521
...obviously I meant...

1105
00:56:41,081 --> 00:56:42,441
.I did.

1106
00:56:45,161 --> 00:56:47,961
I had to make them pay
for what I discovered.

1107
00:56:51,521 --> 00:56:53,321
They lied to us...

1108
00:56:55,721 --> 00:56:58,281
...the founding fathers
of Gallifrey.

1109
00:57:00,721 --> 00:57:03,001
Everything we were told
was a lie.

1110
00:57:05,121 --> 00:57:07,041
We are not who we think,

1111
00:57:07,161 --> 00:57:08,681
you or 1.

1112
00:57:08,801 --> 00:57:11,681
The whole existence
of our species...

1113
00:57:13,001 --> 00:57:16,001
...built on the lie
of the timeless child.

1114
00:57:18,601 --> 00:57:21,601
REMNANTS:
Child...child...child...

1115
00:57:22,801 --> 00:57:24,241
O Do you see it?

1116
00:57:25,641 --> 00:57:29,241
It's buried deep
in all our memories...

1117
00:57:30,241 --> 00:57:31,961
...in our identity.

1118
00:57:33,281 --> 00:57:35,761
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

1119
00:57:37,721 --> 00:57:39,241
I'd tell you more...

1120
00:57:40,441 --> 00:57:41,441
...but..

1121
00:57:47,041 --> 00:57:49,481
...but why would I make it
easy for you?

1122
00:57:51,481 --> 00:57:53,481
It wasn't for me.

1123
00:57:59,201 --> 00:58:00,561
(GROANS)

1124
00:58:09,521 --> 00:58:11,401
YAZ: You OK?
You're really quiet,

1125
00:58:11,521 --> 00:58:13,121
RYAN: Yeah. You have been
for days now.

1126
00:58:13,241 --> 00:58:15,361
They're right. Five planets,
you've barely said a word.

1127
00:58:15,481 --> 00:58:17,161
I'm fine!

1128
00:58:17,281 --> 00:58:18,961
Why don't you ever
share anything with us?

1129
00:58:19,081 --> 00:58:20,601
I share stuff!

1130
00:58:20,721 --> 00:58:22,761
GRAHAM:;
Not about yourself, though.

1131
00:58:22,881 --> 00:58:24,921
RYAN: Yeah, you know
everything about us.

1132
00:58:25,041 --> 00:58:26,321
YAZ: And we know
nothing about you.

1133
00:58:26,441 --> 00:58:27,641
GRAHAM: Mm.

1134
00:58:28,961 --> 00:58:30,721
Fine.

1135
00:58:32,681 --> 00:58:34,281
What do you want to know?

1136
00:58:39,321 --> 00:58:42,161
Who are you, Doc?
I mean, really.

1137
00:58:46,201 --> 00:58:48,521
I was born on a planet
called Gallifrey

1138
00:58:48,641 --> 00:58:50,881
in the constellation
of Kasterborous.

1139
00:58:52,441 --> 00:58:54,721
I'm a Time Lord.

1140
00:58:54,841 --> 00:58:56,681
I can regenerate my body.

1141
00:58:57,921 --> 00:59:00,201
I stole this TARDIS
and I ran away.

1142
00:59:00,321 --> 00:59:02,281
I've been travelling
ever since.

1143
00:59:04,281 --> 00:59:06,721
The Master was
one of my oldest friends.

1144
00:59:08,281 --> 00:59:10,081
We went very different ways.

1145
00:59:12,641 --> 00:59:14,041
Questions?

1146
00:59:21,561 --> 00:59:22,641
Loads.

1147
00:59:23,681 --> 00:59:26,241
Can we visit...your home?

1148
00:59:29,281 --> 00:59:31,401
Another time.

1149
01:00:18,481 --> 01:00:20,841
TANNOY: Welcome
to Tranquillity Spa.

1150
01:00:20,961 --> 01:00:22,681
Why would you need to defend
a holiday spa

1151
01:00:22,801 --> 01:00:23,801
with an ionic membrane?

1152
01:00:23,921 --> 01:00:25,441
I'm sure it's nothing
to worry about.

1153
01:00:25,561 --> 01:00:26,961
We're not safe out here.

